body.p:
—Mauritania has signed a peace
                agreement with the Polisario and
                several thousand Moroccan troops have apparently been withdrawn from Mauritania;

—Morocco is now using a defensive
                “garrison” strategy, the offensive “hot pursuit” strategy appears to have
                failed;

—What started as a popular movement for Moroccans and the King in late 1975 has now
                turned into a risky venture in which many, including perhaps the King himself,
                perceive the monarchy to be in trouble, and under attack;

—King Hassan has been angered by
                American refusal of arms for the Sahara war but at the same time he seems to
                appreciate the fact that U.S. arms cannot turn the war around in his favor;

—support for and good
                    relations with a strong, moderate Morocco free of its conflict in the Western Sahara and thereby free to play
                a more active role in the peace process;
